description:
This is a 2014 comic book created as a collaboration between Dark Horse Comics and the video game developers of Sega and The Creative Assembly. It serves as a prequel to the game of the same name, and its plot consists of several intertwining stories that occur aboard the Sevastopol Station before Amanda Ripley's arrival in the game.

The comic was given away for free exclusively at San Diego Comic-Con 2014, PAX Prime 2014, and London EGX 2014, but a digital copy was also available as a pre-order bonus for the game.
name: Alien: Isolation
